<span id="freeTextContainer10497241072031630765">I watched this film as a teenager never realising until recently it was a book. I was sucked into this on the opening scenes, the attic where the paper flowers blow sucked me in and wouldn&apos;t let me out in the same way as the characters couldn&apos;t leave. <br/><br/>This was a really dark read for its time and using a taboo trope that raises eyebrows now i can only imagine the hype of the 70&apos;s. <br/><br/>I will continue this series, its very readable, the words flow and i flew through the book. While at the time this wa</span>
  <span id="freeText10497241072031630765" style="display:none">I watched this film as a teenager never realising until recently it was a book. I was sucked into this on the opening scenes, the attic where the paper flowers blow sucked me in and wouldn't let me out in the same way as the characters couldn't leave. <br /><br />This was a really dark read for its time and using a taboo trope that raises eyebrows now i can only imagine the hype of the 70's. <br /><br />I will continue this series, its very readable, the words flow and i flew through the book. While at the time this was probably considered adult, i think this reads and feels very YA in today's society. </span>
