        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3111178177" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2212395324652274009">When I was a kid EVERYBODY was talking about this book. A gothic horror with dollops of terror... as a woman hides her children in the attic of her child-unfriendly new partner... for years!!! This Gothic horror mega-best selling novel by <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/1353301.V_C__Andrews' title='V.C. Andrews' rel='nofollow noopener'>V.C. Andrews</a> is the first book in her Dollanganger Series. Written in the first-person, from the point of view of Cathy Dollanganger, one of the children in the attic. Such a clever idea, superbly executed to create a phenomenon without being seen (or read) as </span>
  <span id="freeText2212395324652274009" style="display:none">When I was a kid EVERYBODY was talking about this book. A gothic horror with dollops of terror... as a woman hides her children in the attic of her child-unfriendly new partner... for years!!! This Gothic horror mega-best selling novel by <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/1353301.V_C__Andrews" title="V.C. Andrews" rel="nofollow noopener">V.C. Andrews</a> is the first book in her Dollanganger Series. Written in the first-person, from the point of view of Cathy Dollanganger, one of the children in the attic. Such a clever idea, superbly executed to create a phenomenon without being seen (or read) as tacky or tawdry, despite the main themes of this series being set around child abuse and much much more. 7 out of 12<br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1577810522ra/28694523.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><b>2003 read</b></span>
