<div id="review_4359701502" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4359701502" />
    <a title="Rambling Redhead" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/143417957-rambling-redhead"><img alt="Rambling Redhead" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1643978923p2/143417957.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4359701502?book_show_action=true">Nov 27, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Rambling Redhead" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Rambling Redhead" href="/user/show/143417957-rambling-redhead">Rambling Redhead</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/143417957-rambling-redhead?shelf=classics">classics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/143417957-rambling-redhead?shelf=young-adult">young-adult</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/143417957-rambling-redhead?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4359701502" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8785130757294607057">I read this one a few times in my teens. I know a lot of parents forbid their kids to even think about this book, but I was lucky that I wasn&apos;t one of them. Have to admit, it was kind of racy for an average 13-year-old. However, I wasn&apos;t average and was too busy having nightmares about King&apos;s It by the time I got to this one. Andrews introduced us to 4 kids that are timeless. Even to this day, I can mention the title of this book to anyone, and we can have a discussion. We will never forget Cath</span>
  <span id="freeText8785130757294607057" style="display:none">I read this one a few times in my teens. I know a lot of parents forbid their kids to even think about this book, but I was lucky that I wasn't one of them. Have to admit, it was kind of racy for an average 13-year-old. However, I wasn't average and was too busy having nightmares about King's It by the time I got to this one. Andrews introduced us to 4 kids that are timeless. Even to this day, I can mention the title of this book to anyone, and we can have a discussion. We will never forget Cathy, Chris, the twins and their struggle being locked away in the attic in an attempt to erase away their existence. If you haven't read this book, you need to go get it now. <br /></span>
